					<div id=3D"contentSub"><div id=3D"mw-content-subtitle"></div></div>
				=09
				=09
					<div id=3D"mw-content-text" class=3D"mw-body-content"><div class=3D"mw=
-content-ltr mw-parser-output" lang=3D"en" dir=3D"ltr"><div class=3D"shortd=
escription nomobile noexcerpt noprint searchaux" style=3D"display:none">Sta=
tistical amount</div>
<div role=3D"note" class=3D"hatnote navigation-not-searchable">For broader =
coverage of this topic, see <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Weight=
ed_average" title=3D"Weighted average">Weighted average</a>.</div>
<p>The <b>weighted arithmetic mean</b> is similar to an ordinary <a href=3D=
"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Arithmetic_mean" title=3D"Arithmetic mean">a=
rithmetic mean</a> (the most common type of <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia=
.org/wiki/Average" title=3D"Average">average</a>), except that instead of e=
ach of the data points contributing equally to the final average, some data=
 points contribute more than others. The notion of weighted mean plays a ro=
le in <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Descriptive_statistics" titl=
e=3D"Descriptive statistics">descriptive statistics</a> and also occurs in =
a more general form in several other areas of <a href=3D"https://en.wikiped=
ia.org/wiki/Mathematics" title=3D"Mathematics">mathematics</a>.
</p><p>If all the weights are equal, then the weighted mean is the same as =
the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Arithmetic_mean" title=3D"Arit=
hmetic mean">arithmetic mean</a>.  While weighted means generally behave in=
 a similar fashion to arithmetic means, they do have a few counterintuitive=
 properties, as captured for instance in <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.or=
g/wiki/Simpson%27s_paradox" title=3D"Simpson's paradox">Simpson's paradox</=
a>.
</p>
<meta property=3D"mw:PageProp/toc">
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading2"><h2 id=3D"Examples">Examples</h2><spa=
n class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><=
a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DWeighted_arithmetic_=
mean&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D1" title=3D"Edit section: Examples"><s=
pan>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></=
div>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Basic_example">Basic exampl=
e</h3><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket"=
>[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DWeighted_a=
rithmetic_mean&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D2" title=3D"Edit section: Ba=
sic example"><span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]<=
/span></span></div>
<p>Given two school <span class=3D"nowrap">classes<span style=3D"white-spac=
e: nowrap;">=E2=80=89</span>=E2=80=94<span style=3D"white-space: nowrap;">=
=E2=80=89</span>one</span> with 20 students, one with 30 <span class=3D"now=
rap">students<span style=3D"white-space: nowrap;">=E2=80=89</span>=E2=80=94=
<span style=3D"white-space: nowrap;">=E2=80=89</span>and</span> test grades=
 in each class as follows:
</p>
<dl><dd>Morning class =3D {62, 67, 71, 74, 76, 77, 78, 79, 79, 80, 80, 81, =
81, 82, 83, 84, 86, 89, 93, 98}</dd></dl>
<p><span style=3D"line-height:2;"></span>
</p>
<dl><dd>Afternoon class =3D {81, 82, 83, 84, 85, 86, 87, 87, 88, 88, 89, 89=
, 89, 90, 90, 90, 90, 91, 91, 91, 92, 92, 93, 93, 94, 95, 96, 97, 98, 99}</=
dd></dl>
<p>The mean for the morning class is 80 and the mean of the afternoon class=
 is 90. The unweighted mean of the two means is 85. However, this does not =
account for the difference in number of students in each class (20 versus 3=
0); hence the value of 85 does not reflect the average student grade (indep=
endent of class). The average student grade can be obtained by averaging al=
l the grades, without regard to classes (add all the grades up and divide b=
y the total number of students):
<span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-block"><span class=3D"mwe-=
math-mathml-display mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;"><math di=
splay=3D"block" xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\d=
isplaystyle {\bar {x}}=3D{\frac {4300}{50}}=3D86.}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mover>
              <mi>x</mi>
              <mo stretchy=3D"false">=C2=AF<!-- =C2=AF --></mo>
            </mover>
          </mrow>
        </mrow>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mfrac>
            <mn>4300</mn>
            <mn>50</mn>
          </mfrac>
        </mrow>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <mn>86.</mn>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle {\bar {x}}=3D=
{\frac {4300}{50}}=3D86.}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/f5f81a6b338682edc2ff1402a9d176fa20fe6e42" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-display mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertica=
l-align: -1.838ex; width:15.984ex; height:5.176ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle {=
\bar {x}}=3D{\frac {4300}{50}}=3D86.}"></span>
</p><p>Or, this can be accomplished by weighting the class means by the num=
ber of students in each class. The larger class is given more "weight":
</p>
<dl><dd><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span clas=
s=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;">=
<math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyl=
e {\bar {x}}=3D{\frac {(20\times 80)+(30\times 90)}{20+30}}=3D86.}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mover>
              <mi>x</mi>
              <mo stretchy=3D"false">=C2=AF<!-- =C2=AF --></mo>
            </mover>
          </mrow>
        </mrow>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mfrac>
            <mrow>
              <mo stretchy=3D"false">(</mo>
              <mn>20</mn>
              <mo>=C3=97<!-- =C3=97 --></mo>
              <mn>80</mn>
              <mo stretchy=3D"false">)</mo>
              <mo>+</mo>
              <mo stretchy=3D"false">(</mo>
              <mn>30</mn>
              <mo>=C3=97<!-- =C3=97 --></mo>
              <mn>90</mn>
              <mo stretchy=3D"false">)</mo>
            </mrow>
            <mrow>
              <mn>20</mn>
              <mo>+</mo>
              <mn>30</mn>
            </mrow>
          </mfrac>
        </mrow>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <mn>86.</mn>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle {\bar {x}}=3D=
{\frac {(20\times 80)+(30\times 90)}{20+30}}=3D86.}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/445ef9d88cca8a93f65132de0ddc5ddfa13ef2ea" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical=
-align: -2.005ex; width:32.774ex; height:5.843ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle {\=
bar {x}}=3D{\frac {(20\times 80)+(30\times 90)}{20+30}}=3D86.}"></span></dd=
></dl>
<p>Thus, the weighted mean makes it possible to find the mean average stude=
nt grade without knowing each student's score. Only the class means and the=
 number of students in each class are needed.
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Convex_combination_example"=
>Convex combination example</h3><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=
=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/i=
ndex.php?title=3DWeighted_arithmetic_mean&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D3=
" title=3D"Edit section: Convex combination example"><span>edit</span></a><=
span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p>Since only the <i>relative</i> weights are relevant, any weighted mean c=
an be expressed using coefficients that sum to one. Such a linear combinati=
on is called a <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Convex_combination"=
 title=3D"Convex combination">convex combination</a>.
</p><p>Using the previous example, we would get the following weights:
</p>
<dl><dd><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span clas=
s=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;">=
<math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyl=
e {\frac {20}{20+30}}=3D0.4}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mfrac>
            <mn>20</mn>
            <mrow>
              <mn>20</mn>
              <mo>+</mo>
              <mn>30</mn>
            </mrow>
          </mfrac>
        </mrow>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <mn>0.4</mn>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle {\frac {20}{2=
0+30}}=3D0.4}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/c61c40dd8cc09f1c7dcdbc19547bbafc773714fb" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical=
-align: -2.005ex; width:14.397ex; height:5.343ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle {\=
frac {20}{20+30}}=3D0.4}"></span></dd></dl>
<dl><dd><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span clas=
s=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;">=
<math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyl=
e {\frac {30}{20+30}}=3D0.6}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mfrac>
            <mn>30</mn>
            <mrow>
              <mn>20</mn>
              <mo>+</mo>
              <mn>30</mn>
            </mrow>
          </mfrac>
        </mrow>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <mn>0.6</mn>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle {\frac {30}{2=
0+30}}=3D0.6}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/fb99d08b4e26daf1f7107925513b2502533a77bb" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical=
-align: -2.005ex; width:14.397ex; height:5.343ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle {\=
frac {30}{20+30}}=3D0.6}"></span></dd></dl>
<p>Then, apply the weights like this:
</p>
<dl><dd><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span clas=
s=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;">=
<math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyl=
e {\bar {x}}=3D(0.4\times 80)+(0.6\times 90)=3D86.}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mover>
              <mi>x</mi>
              <mo stretchy=3D"false">=C2=AF<!-- =C2=AF --></mo>
            </mover>
          </mrow>
        </mrow>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <mo stretchy=3D"false">(</mo>
        <mn>0.4</mn>
        <mo>=C3=97<!-- =C3=97 --></mo>
        <mn>80</mn>
        <mo stretchy=3D"false">)</mo>
        <mo>+</mo>
        <mo stretchy=3D"false">(</mo>
        <mn>0.6</mn>
        <mo>=C3=97<!-- =C3=97 --></mo>
        <mn>90</mn>
        <mo stretchy=3D"false">)</mo>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <mn>86.</mn>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle {\bar {x}}=3D=
(0.4\times 80)+(0.6\times 90)=3D86.}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/63befaebd3a30c048762c5b6c9a03b9bbe51f7a9" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical=
-align: -0.838ex; width:33.231ex; height:2.843ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle {\=
bar {x}}=3D(0.4\times 80)+(0.6\times 90)=3D86.}"></span></dd></dl>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading2"><h2 id=3D"Mathematical_definition">Ma=
thematical definition</h2><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-=
editsection-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.ph=
p?title=3DWeighted_arithmetic_mean&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D4" title=
=3D"Edit section: Mathematical definition"><span>edit</span></a><span class=
=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p>Formally, the weighted mean of a non-empty finite <a href=3D"https://en.=
wikipedia.org/wiki/Tuple" title=3D"Tuple">tuple</a> of data <span class=3D"=
mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span class=3D"mwe-math-mathml-in=
line mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;"><math xmlns=3D"http://w=
ww.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyle \left(x_{1},x_{2},\do=
ts ,x_{n}\right)}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mrow>
          <mo>(</mo>
          <mrow>
            <msub>
              <mi>x</mi>
              <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                <mn>1</mn>
              </mrow>
            </msub>
            <mo>,</mo>
            <msub>
              <mi>x</mi>
              <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                <mn>2</mn>
              </mrow>
            </msub>
            <mo>,</mo>
            <mo>=E2=80=A6<!-- =E2=80=A6 --></mo>
            <mo>,</mo>
            <msub>
              <mi>x</mi>
              <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                <mi>n</mi>
              </mrow>
            </msub>
          </mrow>
          <mo>)</mo>
        </mrow>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle \left(x_{1},x=
_{2},\dots ,x_{n}\right)}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/7d14087100ff74feb22f55788cffef4af1d42c79" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical=
-align: -0.838ex; width:15.337ex; height:2.843ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle \l=
eft(x_{1},x_{2},\dots ,x_{n}\right)}"></span>,
with corresponding non-negative <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/We=
ight_function" title=3D"Weight function">weights</a> <span class=3D"mwe-mat=
h-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span class=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mw=
e-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;"><math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.o=
rg/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyle \left(w_{1},w_{2},\dots ,w_{=
n}\right)}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mrow>
          <mo>(</mo>
          <mrow>
            <msub>
              <mi>w</mi>
              <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                <mn>1</mn>
              </mrow>
            </msub>
            <mo>,</mo>
            <msub>
              <mi>w</mi>
              <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                <mn>2</mn>
              </mrow>
            </msub>
            <mo>,</mo>
            <mo>=E2=80=A6<!-- =E2=80=A6 --></mo>
            <mo>,</mo>
            <msub>
              <mi>w</mi>
              <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                <mi>n</mi>
