<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Variance">Variance</h3><spa=
n class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><=
a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DWeighted_arithmetic_=
mean&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D8" title=3D"Edit section: Variance"><s=
pan>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></=
div>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading4"><h4 id=3D"Simple_i.i.d._case">Simple =
i.i.d. case</h4><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsectio=
n-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3D=
Weighted_arithmetic_mean&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D9" title=3D"Edit s=
ection: Simple i.i.d. case"><span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsect=
ion-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p>When treating the weights as constants, and having a sample of <i>n</i> =
observations from <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Uncorrelatedness=
_(probability_theory)" title=3D"Uncorrelatedness (probability theory)">unco=
rrelated</a> <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Random_variables" cla=
ss=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Random variables">random variables</a>, all wit=
h the same <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Variance" title=3D"Vari=
ance">variance</a> and <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Expected_va=
lue" title=3D"Expected value">expectation</a> (as is the case for <a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Independent_and_identically_distributed_r=
andom_variables" title=3D"Independent and identically distributed random va=
riables">i.i.d</a> random variables), then the variance of the weighted mea=
n can be estimated as the multiplication of the unweighted variance by <a h=
ref=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Design_effect#Unequal_selection_probab=
ilities" title=3D"Design effect">Kish's design effect</a> (see <a href=3D"h=
ttps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Design_effect#Assumptions_and_proofs" title=3D=
"Design effect">proof</a>):
</p>
<dl><dd><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span clas=
s=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;">=
<math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyl=
