strapping (statistics)">bootstrapping</a> methods, the following (variance =
estimation of ratio-mean using <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tay=
lor_series" title=3D"Taylor series">Taylor series</a> linearization) is a r=
easonable estimation for the square of the standard error of the mean (when=
 used in the context of measuring chemical constituents):<sup id=3D"cite_re=
f-5" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Weighted_=
arithmetic_mean#cite_note-5"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>4<span cl=
ass=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup><sup class=3D"reference nowrap"><spa=
n title=3D"Page / location: 1186">:=E2=80=8A1186=E2=80=8A</span></sup>
</p>
