          </mrow>
        </mstyle>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle \textstyle \m=
athbf {C} }</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/cffb901ac3e2daf5c18c245bcb666023902cfd69" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical=
-align: -0.338ex; width:1.931ex; height:2.176ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle \te=
xtstyle \mathbf {C} }"></span>, with Bessel's correction, is given by:<sup =
id=3D"cite_ref-PRICE-1972_9-1" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wi=
kipedia.org/wiki/Weighted_arithmetic_mean#cite_note-PRICE-1972-9"><span cla=
ss=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>8<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup=
>
</p>
<dl><dd><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span clas=
s=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;">=
<math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyl=
e \mathbf {C} =3D{\frac {\sum _{i=3D1}^{N}w_{i}\left(\mathbf {x} _{i}-\mu ^=
{*}\right)^{T}\left(\mathbf {x} _{i}-\mu ^{*}\right)}{V_{1}-1}}.}">
