es changing the data's mean and variance and thus leading to a <a href=3D"h=
ttps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Base_rate_fallacy" title=3D"Base rate fallacy"=
>loss of the base rate</a> (the population count, which is a requirement fo=
r Bessel's correction).
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading4"><h4 id=3D"Reliability_weights_2">Reli=
ability weights</h4><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editse=
ction-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?titl=
e=3DWeighted_arithmetic_mean&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D22" title=3D"E=
dit section: Reliability weights"><span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-ed=
itsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p>In the case of <i>reliability weights</i>, the weights are <a href=3D"ht=
tps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Normalizing_constant" title=3D"Normalizing cons=
tant">normalized</a>:
</p>
<dl><dd><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span clas=
s=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;">=
<math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyl=
e V_{1}=3D\sum _{i=3D1}^{N}w_{i}=3D1.}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
