ion=3D27" title=3D"Edit section: Weighted averages of functions"><span>edit=
</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p>The concept of weighted average can be extended to functions.<sup id=3D"=
cite_ref-12" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/W=
eighted_arithmetic_mean#cite_note-12"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>=
11<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> Weighted averages of func=
tions play an important role in the systems of weighted differential and in=
tegral calculus.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-13" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"http=
s://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Weighted_arithmetic_mean#cite_note-13"><span clas=
